### 5.3 Privacy Act Compliance

As an organisation exceeding the $3 million annual revenue threshold, {{ business_name }} is bound by the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs) under the Privacy Act 1988. All AI use involving personal information must comply with:

- **APP 3** — Collection of personal information must be necessary and lawful
- **APP 6** — Use and disclosure limited to the primary purpose of collection
- **APP 8** — Cross-border disclosure restrictions apply to AI tools hosted overseas
- **APP 11** — Reasonable steps to protect personal information from misuse
{% endif %}

{% if annual_revenue == "under_3m" %}
### 5.3 Small Business Exemption Status

{{ business_name }} currently falls under the small business exemption (annual revenue under $3 million) and may not be bound by all Australian Privacy Principles. However, this exemption is under active review and may be removed by future legislative reform. {{ business_name }} adopts these AI use controls as best practice and to ensure readiness for any change in regulatory status. Note that certain obligations (such as the statutory tort for serious invasion of privacy) apply regardless of revenue — see Section 12.
{% endif %}

