## 5A. APP 8 — Cross-Border Disclosure Obligations

{{ business_name }} uses the following AI tools that are hosted or operated overseas:

{% for tool in ai_tools_overseas %}
- {{ tool }}
{% endfor %}

Under **Australian Privacy Principle 8**, before disclosing personal information to an overseas recipient (including via an overseas-hosted AI tool), {{ business_name }} must:

1. Take reasonable steps to ensure the overseas recipient handles personal information in accordance with the APPs
2. Assess whether the recipient country has substantially similar privacy protections, or obtain the individual's informed consent
3. Be accountable for any acts or practices of the overseas recipient that breach the APPs, as if {{ business_name }} had committed the breach itself
4. Maintain a record of all overseas disclosures, including the country, recipient, and purpose

**Staff obligations:**
- Do **not** input personal information into any overseas AI tool unless a cross-border disclosure assessment has been completed and approved
- Contact {{ ai_governance_contact | default("the AI Governance Contact", true) }} before processing personal information with any of the overseas tools listed above
- Document each instance of cross-border data disclosure in the AI usage register
{% endif %}

