## Appendix A: Definitions and Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| AI Tool | Any software system that uses artificial intelligence, machine learning, or large language models to process data, generate content, or assist decision-making |
| Shadow AI | AI tools used by staff without organisational knowledge, approval, or oversight |
| Personal Information | Information or an opinion about an identified individual, or an individual who is reasonably identifiable (Privacy Act 1988 s 6(1)) |
| Sensitive Information | A subset of personal information including health, biometric, genetic data, and information about racial or ethnic origin, political opinions, or criminal records |
| APP | Australian Privacy Principle — the 13 principles governing personal information handling under the Privacy Act 1988 |
| ACL | Australian Consumer Law — Schedule 2 of the Competition and Consumer Act 2010 |
| POLA Act | Privacy and Other Legislation Amendment Act 2024 — introduces automated decision transparency and statutory tort |
| DPA | Data Processing Agreement — a contract establishing data handling obligations between an organisation and a vendor |
| NDB | Notifiable Data Breaches scheme — mandatory reporting of eligible data breaches to the OAIC |
| PIA | Privacy Impact Assessment — a systematic assessment of privacy risks |
| OAIC | Office of the Australian Information Commissioner — Australia's national privacy regulator |
| Cross-Border Disclosure | Disclosing personal information to an overseas recipient, including via overseas-hosted AI tools (APP 8) |
| Statutory Tort | A civil cause of action for serious invasion of privacy introduced by the POLA Act 2024 |
| AI6 | The Australian Government's 6 Essential Practices for safe and responsible AI |

